<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Parliament to Discuss Transit Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The issue of transshipment of
Indian goods through Bangladesh will be discussed in the next
session of the Bangladeshi parliament scheduled for August 29, the
BSS news agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting of the National Advisory Committee on
Trade and Industry on Sunday, Minister for Commerce and Industries
Tofail Ahmed welcomed the opposition to the debate both in and
outside the parliament on the issue.
</P>
<P>
He said the government is taking all initiatives to make the
issue more transparent and actions more accountable to the people.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi government has approved in principle a proposal
for examining and discussing the transit issue.
</P>
<P>
Right after the approval was made, the major opposition party
in the parliament, the Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP)
denounced the government decision, saying it "would ultimately
jeopardize security" of the country.
</P>
<P>
The BNP-led alliance has decided to conduct a series of
activities to force the government to abandon the decision.
</P>
<P>
However, some business leaders said that the transit would give
enormous direct and indirect dividend to the national economy, and
they urge the government to finalize the transit issue as early as
possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
