<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Contracts for Employment Outside HK Must be Attested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The public here in Hong Kong
have been reminded that every contract for employment outside Hong
Kong must be signed by the employer or his representative and the
employee before the employee leaves Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The contract must contain all the particulars required by the
Contracts for Employment Outside Hong Kong Ordinance to define the
rights and obligations of both parties and be presented to the
Commissioner for Labor for attestation before the employee's
departure.
</P>
<P>
Labor officer of the external employment service of the Labor
Department Lam Chow-Laiwah said Sunday that the Ordinance applied
to all contracts entered into in Hong Kong by manual employees and
those non-manual employees with monthly wages not exceeding 20,000
HK dollars who were employed to work outside Hong Kong by
employers who were not in Hong Kong and were not running a
business locally.
</P>
<P>
"An employer or his agent will commit an offense if he fails to
enter into a written contract or present the written contract for
attestation by the Commissioner for Labor before the employee
leaves Hong Kong," said the officer.
</P>
<P>
"Moreover, a person will commit an offense if he induces an
employee to enter into a contract which does not comply with the
Ordinance or leave Hong Kong to take up employment before the
contract is attested," she stressed.
</P>
<P>
The maximum penalty for each offense is a fine of 50,000 HK
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
