<HEADLINE> Singapore Economy Grows 6.7 Pct in 2nd Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore economy recorded
a vigorous growth of 6.7 percent in the second quarter of this
year, Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In a National Day Message delivered Sunday evening, Goh said
the economy expanded by 3.7 percent in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
He said the Trade and Industry Ministry has revised upwards the
growth forecast for the whole of this year to 4-5 percent.
</P>
