<HEADLINE> People's Daily On Increasing Fight Against Falun Gong Cult </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- People's Daily will carry a
commentary tomorrow, urging people to use Marxism, Mao Zedong
Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory to erase the pernicious effects
of the Falun Gong cult.
</P>
<P>
The commentary says that facts have proved that only Marxism,
Mao Zedong Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory can help people
clearly see the importance of the fight against Falun Gong and see
the true nature of its malicious fallacies and save the people who
have been deceived and fooled by Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
People need to use these theories to have an overall
understanding of the internal and international political
background of the campaign against Falun Gong and of the
seriousness, arduousness and complex nature of the fight, it says.
</P>
<P>
It emphasizes that the cult is a mixture of superstition and
pseudo-science that has posed a serious threat to the Communist
Party of China and the state and that the importance of the fight
can never be underestimated.
</P>
<P>
The major reason Falun Gong could deceive so many people was
that it had a complete set of fallacious ideas. Li Hongzhi, its
founder, in his work against science and government clearly made
Marxism and Materialism his targets of attack.
</P>
<P>
This shows that the fight against Falun Gong is a fierce one
for the defence of science and truth, it says, so the importance
of theories can not be neglected for even one moment.
</P>
<P>
Li's fallacies and Falun Gong were by no means an isolated
phenomenon, it says, and the fight against Falun Gong is not
confined to dealing with it organizationally or merely helping
practitioners avoid superstitious and pseudo-scientific thought.
What is more important is increasing socialist spiritual
civilization, ideological and political work, building democracy
and a legal system, and building the Party, it concludes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
