<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Retains Leading Place in China's Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Fushun usurped the
leading place from Shandong Luneng on a 2-1 win over Qingdao
Hainiu on Sunday after the 18th round match of the Chinese first-
division soccer league in Shenyang, Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Shandong is one point trailing to the leaders on 33 points
following a goalless draw with Jilin Aodong at home in Jinan,
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Li Jinyu, who had completed his loan to French side Nancy,
opened the mark for the home side in the injury time of the first
half, before Qu Shengxin extended the lead to 2-0 on a 36th-minute
goal.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao, who moaned near the bottom of the standings, pulled
one back from Qiu Zhonghui four minutes from time.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to a fourth-minute blister strike from midfielder Wei
Qun, Sichuan Quanxing conquered Shanghai Shenhua at home 1-0 to
steal the third place of the league, edging off Shenhua on goal
differential as both teams collected 29 points.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Dalian Wanda had its three winning streak
snapped at home when it was held to a 1-1 draw by Shenyang Haishi.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's other matches, Beijing Guo'an trounced Guangzhou
Songri 3-0, Chongqing Longxin lost to Tianjin Taida 2-1, while
Shenzhen Ping'an beat Wuhan Heart K 1-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
