<DOCNO> XIE19990809.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Hails Barak's Pledge to Start Wye Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
Chairman Yasser Arafat Sunday welcomed Israeli Prime Minister Ehud
Barak's promise to start implementing the Wye River Accord as from
September.
</P>
<P>
Arafat made the remarks at a press conference after meeting
with visiting Qatari Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin Khalifa Al-Thani at
Arafat's presidential office in Gaza. The meeting lasted for one
and a half hours.
</P>
<P>
Hamad, who arrived here in the midday, is the first Arab Gulf
state leader to visit the Palestinian territories.
</P>
<P>
"What is important is the implementation of the provisions on
the building of Gaza seaport, the release of prisoners and the
opening of the safe passage as well as the economic aspects and
the third stage of the Israeli pullout from the West Bank," Arafat
said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat and Barak's predecessor Benjamin Netanyahu signed the
Wye Accord last October in Washington, but hardliner Netanyahu
suspended the agreement in early December.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he expressed regret over the current situation of
the peace process, saying, "up till now, there is a lot of talks
about peace, but the implementation of the Wye Accord is
repeatedly deferred."
</P>
<P>
"What we ask for is the sincere and precise implementation of
the signed agreements in order to be able to establish fair and
comprehensive peace in the region," Arafat added.
</P>
<P>
"We call on Barak who adopts the line of (late Israeli Prime
Minister Yitzrak) Rabin to expedite the implementation of the
signed agreements and meet the promises he made to us and to
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak," Arafat underlined.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Hamad said Barak "should immediately put into
force the Wye Accord as he committed."
</P>
<P>
On the Israeli trade office in his country, Hamad said "this
will not infringe on our ties with the Palestinians." "The Qatari
people stood by the Palestinian people since its crisis," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Qatari emir promised that his country would continue its
assistance to the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Talks between Arafat and Hamad dealt with a score of issues of
common interest, including the peace process, bilateral economic
cooperation and Qatari financial aid to the PNA, according to
Palestinian sources.
</P>
<P>
Hamad left Gaza later in the day and flew to Beirut to continue
regional tour.
</P>
<P>
Qatar opened a trade represtation office in Gaza in November,
1995, and provided 5 million U.S. dollars to the PNA in aid since
the PNA return to the Palestinian territories in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Late last year, an air route between Gaza and Doha opened with
one regular flight every week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
