<HEADLINE> Iran Commemorates Reporter, Diplomats Killed in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held here on
Sunday to commemorate Mahmoud Saremi, a correspondent of the
official Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) and eight Iranian
diplomats killed in Afghanistan by Taliban troops.
</P>
<P>
Saremi and the diplomats were killed soon after Taliban troops
seized Mazar-i-Sharif, a stronghold of the opposition forces in
northern Afghanistan on August 8, 1998.
</P>
