<DOCNO> XIE19990809.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Steel Production on Upswing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The first five months of this
year witnessed a steady growth of China's steel production with
the output growing a year-on-year 6.7 percent to reach 49.2
million tons, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of steel products between January and May hit 47.5
million tons, surging 15.5 percent on an annual basis, the bureau
said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, production of pig iron grew by 5.3 percent
over the same period last year to reach 49.9 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The period also saw a year-on-year increase of 8.7 percent in
the output of non-ferrous metals, which chalked up 2.6 million
tons.
</P>
<P>
During the January-May period, the output of aluminum oxide hit
1.55 million tons, up 16 percent on an annual basis, and that of
aluminum products hit 573,900 tons, surging 17 percent.
</P>
<P>
The production of copper products increased by 16 percent over
the same period last year to reach 487,100 tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
