<HEADLINE> Military World Games Open in Zagreb </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Croatian taekwondo athlete Natasa Vezmar lit the Torch of Peace
at the opening ceremony, sending nearly 60,000 spectators into
ecstasy at the Maksimir Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Eighty-one countries have sent delegations to the Games, which
are organized by the International Military Sports Council and
competed by the athletes in the military forces.
</P>
<P>
Croatia's President Franjo Tudjman declared the Games open
after the International Olympic Committee President Juan Antonio
Samaranch addressed the audience. 
</P>
</TEXT>
