<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Johansson Wins Canadian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Eleventh-seeded Thomas Johansson
of Sweden won the Canadian Open by beating third-seeded Yevgeny
Kafelnikov of Russia 1-6, 6-3, 6-3 in Montreal on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Johansson, 24, won the biggest title of his career at the ATP
Super 9 event, taking home a winner's prize of 161,000 U.S.
dollars and enough ranking points to move up to 17th from 22nd.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov's runner-up showing moved him from fourth to second,
but he has now lost all four times he has reached a Super 9 final.
</P>
<P>
The two hour, two minute match was a onesided affair in the
early going. Johansson was error prone but he improved
dramatically in the second and third sets.
</P>
<P>
In the last few games of the final set, he hit several
explosive ground strokes that streaked past an increasingly
frustrated Kafelnikov. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
