<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis Beats Venus Williams to Win in California </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 8 (Xinhua) - Martina Hingis of Switzerland
trounced American Venus Williams 6-4, 6-0 to win the 520,000 U.S.
dollars T.I.G.Classic tennis tournament in Carlsbad, California on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The second-seeded Hingis took the final nine games of the 61-
minute match from the fourth-seeded American.
</P>
<P>
Hingis had regained the world number spot Saturday by crushing
seventh-seeded Amanda Coetzer after Williams stunned Lindsay
Davenport in the first semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Hingis lost the top ranking to reigning Wimbledon champion
Davenport on July 5 and decided to take a break from the game.
After a brief vacation, she began an extensive weight-training
program while pondering her passion for the game. 
</P>
