<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Falun Gong Causes Practitioner's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- More evidences has appeared that
Falun Gong has harmed the physical and mental health of
practitioners as well as caused the death of several people.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Weimin, a head of a Falun Gong training center in Anhui
Province, died of a stroke while practicing Falun Gong on October
20, 1994. His wife, Liu Bizhen, said that she had never thought
that her 56-year-old husband could die of Falun Gong after
practicing it for only half a year.
</P>
<P>
She said that on the day Jiang suffered a stroke, the deputy-
head of the Anhui training station repeatedly phoned the Falun
Dafa Research Society in Beijing to ask Li Hongzhi, the founder of
Falun Gong, to give a helping hand, but got no response.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that this tragic incident proved that the powerful
Falun Gong was a lie.
</P>
<P>
Li Dekun is another victim in Hefei, capital of Anhui Province.
He began to practise Falun Gong in 1998 in the hope of curing a
disease. But after a year of practising, his physical condition
didn't improve and in fact began to deteriorate. This evidence
showed him that Falun Gong had nothing to do with treating disease
or illness and made him determined to break all connections with
it.
</P>
<P>
More Falun Gong victims have been found in the city of Anshan
in Liaoning Province, where doctors at the Kangning Mental
Hospital say that they have received ten patients who were
suffering from mental problems resulting from Falun Gong. They
warn people to be on guard against Falun Gong's destruction of the
human spirit and say that only science can bring good health to
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
