<HEADLINE> China's Output of Electric Appliances up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The production of household
electric appliances grew steadily in the first five months this
year, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of color TV sets from January to May hit 16.5
million units, soaring a year-on-year 31.5 percent, and that of
household refrigerators went up 12.3 percent to 4.8 million units.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures from the bureau show that the country
produced 6.5 million air conditioners during the period, jumping
up 56.4 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the output of washing machines edged up 1.6
percent to 5.4 million units.
</P>
<P>
China has taken measures to stimulate domestic demand in a bid
to minimize the impact of the Asian financial crisis. Its anti-
smuggling drive has also promoted sales of China-made household
electric appliances, according to market sources.
</P>
<P>
There is also a great potential in the vast rural market where
80 percent of China's 1.2 billion people live, they said.
</P>
</TEXT>
