<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Geneticist Disputes Falun Gong's Claims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shanghai, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Tan Jiazhen, a prominent Chinese
geneticist, said that the fallacies of the Falun Gong cult fly in
the face of science and truth and should be eliminated.
</P>
<P>
The 90-year-old Tan said that man's evolution has been
confirmed by study over the centuries but many people were still
being cheated by Falun Gong's fallacies and the need to promote
scientific thought among people has become more urgent than ever.
</P>
<P>
It is nonsense to say that man dropped from the universe and
that evil people fell on the earth, he said, but Li Hongzhi, the
founder of Falun Gong, fooled people with his theories about the
course of man. Man's evolution from apes is unquestioned, he said,
and Li's theory about how god created man is utterly absurd.
</P>
<P>
Tan said that with the increase in research on genetics, the
cause of a number of diseases has been found and some formerly
incurable diseases can now be treated. But, Li Hongzhi asked sick
people not to go to the doctor and many people died because of a
lack of treatment. He is the real killer, Tan said.
</P>
<P>
Everyone wants a long and healthy life but only the development
of science and technology can achieve this, he said. Scientists
and doctors have made some headway in this and they are working
harder to improve man's immunity to disease and prolong life, he
added.
</P>
<P>
So, the crucial task is to spread scientific knowledge among
the Chinese to increase their ability to tell right from wrong and
to promote materialism and atheism, he concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
