<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Growth of Telecom Industry Slowing Down in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, August 9 (Xinhua) -- China's fast-growing
telecommunications industry showed signs of a slowdown in the
first five months this year, according to the National Bureau of
Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of program-controlled switchboards surged 38 percent
year-on-year to 16.1 million lines between January and May, the
bureau said.
</P>
<P>
However, production of optical communications equipment
plummeted 38.2 percent on an annual basis to 4,884 units, and that
of carrier communications equipment dropped 18.2 percent to 2,375
units.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the country produced 10.7 million sets of
mobile communications equipment during the period, a drastic
increase of 45.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Production of computers during the time enjoyed a 163-percent
increase to a total of 1,208 units while that of micro-computers
surged 59.8 percent to 1.38 million.
</P>
<P>
Computer manufacturers in China have enjoyed a rapid growth
these years, and recent surveys show that more and more Chinese
are planning to buy their own personal computers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
