<HEADLINE> Guangdong Leads in Industrial Output Value </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province, the economic
powerhouse in south China, led the country in terms of industrial
output value in the first five months this year, according to the
National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures offered by the bureau show that Guangdong's
industrial output value in the January-May period stood at 371
billion yuan (about 45 billion U.S. dollars), surging 15 percent
on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong was followed by east China's Jiangsu Province, with
an industrial output value of 313 billion yuan, and Shanghai
Municipality with 223 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
A pioneer in China's reform and opening up drive, Guangdong has
developed a full-blown processing industry and a large proportion
of its enterprises are export-oriented.  
