<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Communist Party Member's Five-Year Struggle Against Falun Gong(2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He recalled that three leaders of the local Falun Gong training
center came to his office on September 30, 1998 and demanded that
the newspaper apologize for an article about a retired worker who
followed Falun Gong and took his own life by cutting open his
stomach.
</P>
<P>
This proved that the sect was strictly organized and had close
links with well-informed members, Li says. An increasing number of
practitioners began to bother the newspaper just four days after
the article appeared, just as the three leaders had done earlier.
</P>
<P>
They had prepared a statement of apology on the paper's behalf,
Li says, and demanded that it be printed without a word changed.
</P>
<P>
They then organized the protest under orders from the Falun
Dafa Research Society, according to Duan Rongxin, the former head
of the Falun Gong training center in Shijiazhuang, the capital of
Hebei.
</P>
<P>
In Shanxi Province, some prominent writers criticized the
fallacies of the Falun Gong, and Ma Feng, an elderly writer, says
that writers and artists have been responsible for heightening
people's ideological awareness and moral integrity. Otherwise,
decadent ideas and practices can be used to take advantage of
people's weak points, Ma says. He has asked writers to get closer
to the people and to reflect their true thoughts and the reality
of the times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
