<HEADLINE> China Produces More Building Materials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- China's output of building
materials has been on the rise in the first five months this year,
according to latest figures from the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of cement in the January-May period amounted to 200.
4 million tons, up a year-on-year 14.6 percent, and that of plate
glass stood at 68.5 million weight cases, up 7.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
China has stepped up infrastructure construction in a bid to
stimulate domestic demand. Total investment in the construction
sector in the five months hit 3.6 billion yuan (about 433 million
U.S. dollars), surging 30.5 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
