<HEADLINE> Bus Accident Kills 2, Hurts 28 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Two passengers were killed and 28
others injured Sunday in a bus accident in central Sri Lanka
where a private bus in which they were traveling hurtled down a
precipice, said reports reaching here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The private bus which was bound for Gampola from Dunukeulla
fell into the precipice after colliding with a bus belonging to a
Gampola bus company, the reports quoted police as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to police, 11 passengers who were seriously injured
were admitted to nearby hospitals in Peradeniya and Kandy while
the others were treated at the local hospital in Gampola.
</P>
<P>
Police are conducting further investigations into the incident.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
