<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Foreign Trade Reaches Over 1 Bln Dlrs in 4 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's foreign trade, including
the border trade, totaled 1.162 billion U.S. dollars in the first
four months of this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest data published by the country's Central
Statistical Organization, of the total trade volume, imports were
762 million dollars, while exports stood at 399 million dollars,
producing a trade deficit of 363 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
During the four-month period, the import value of capital
goods, consumers goods and intermediate goods, the three major
categories of Myanmar's imported goods, accounted for 51.57
percent, 38.32 percent and 10.11 percent of the total import
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The figures also show that during the period, the import value
of the private sector amounted to 566 million dollars, making up
74.27 percent of the total import, while its export value of the
sector went to 290 million dollars, taking up 72.68 percent of the
total export.
</P>
<P>
The import and export value of the government sector during the
period accounted for only 25.73 percent and 27.32 percent
respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
