<HEADLINE> Two Germans Arrested on Charges of Selling Missile Secrets to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The German federal court confirmed
Sunday that two Germans were arrested on charges of selling
military high-tech secrets to Russia.
</P>
<P>
Eva Schuebel, a spokeswoman of the court, said the two were
arrested at the end of last month and authorities seized a large
number of documents in defense areas, including tank defense
systems.
</P>
<P>
The weekly Focus magazine, to be published Monday, reported
that the two sold documents on the Eurofighter's new missile
system.
</P>
<P>
One of them was an engineer working at a subsidiary of the
German aeronautics company DaimlerChrysler Aerospace. The other
was a businessman who made frequent trips to Moscow.
</P>
<P>
The German Defense Ministry was analyzing the loss to Germany
caused by the case. The German Embassy in Moscow would lodge a
protest to the Russian authorities, the magazine reported.
</P>
</TEXT>
