<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Death Toll in Philippines' Floods Reaches 126 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The death count from last week's
four-day monsoon rains and landslides in the central and northern
Philippines has reached 126, including 46 in a landslide that hit
the Cerry Hills Subdivision in Antipolo city, Manila.
</P>
<P>
According to the National Disaster Coordination Council, the
death toll included 40 casualties in several provinces north of
Manila and 30 others in Manila and surrounding provinces.
</P>
<P>
The floods also swamped 14,093 hectares of farmlands and
fishponds. Damage was placed at 625.89 million pesos (15.64
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Relief agencies reported that many areas in the north,
particularly in Pangasinan, were still submerged in seven feet of
flood waters.
</P>
<P>
The flooding also damaged nearly 11,000 houses. Of more than
70,000 who abandoned their homes, 52,000 are still in evacuation
centers, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasters said intermittent rains were still
expected in the next two weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
