<DOCNO> XIE19990809.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing University Professors Lash out at Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Professors and scholars from the
prestigious Beijing University recently have vowed to fight
against the malicious fallacies of Falun Gong and its founder, Li
Hongzhi.
</P>
<P>
Professor Ye Lang, the chairman of the Philosophy Department,
said that Li Hongzhi's ideas are anti-scientific because he denies
modern science with the excuse that human beings cannot understand
all natural phenomena.
</P>
<P>
Ye pointed out that Falun Gong raised more problems about
scientific knowledge hence the urgent need to strengthen Marxist
philosophy and humanities studies.
</P>
<P>
Professor Zhao Dunhua of the department said that the Falun
Gong cult has made people realize the importance of ruling the
country in accordance with the law. He said that China guarantees
religious freedoms and the freedom to believe in atheism, but some
Falun Gong followers only allow themselves to believe in
superstition and leave no room for people to believe in atheism.
</P>
<P>
The Falun Gong followers have attacked government offices and
news media organizations and have seriously disrupted social order,
Zhao stressed.
</P>
<P>
The professors agree that the whole society should increase
education in popular science and the humanities to help people
immunize themselves against the Falun Gong cult and other
superstitious beliefs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
