<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Indian newspapers Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Times of India:
</P>
<P>
-- Caretaker Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee Sunday ruled
out immediate talks with Pakistan and launched a scathing attack
on the Congress for forcing mid-term elections.
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times:
</P>
<P>
-- Sabotage can not be ruled out in the train collision which
killed over 290 passengers on August 2 in northeast India, Chief
Commissioner of Railway Safety M. Mani said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Hindu:
</P>
<P>
-- The first India-Japan investment dialogue is scheduled to
take place in New Delhi from Tuesday. 
