<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Lease Out 10 More Trains to Private Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The state-run Bangladesh Railway
(BR) is going to lease out service of ten more trains to the
private sector, The New Nation daily newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The BR has already floated tenders in this regard, and the
other formalities to lease out the trains will be completed within
a short time, a top ranking official source of the BR was quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The earnings from the ten trains which are going to be leased
out to the private sector would be doubled than that of the trains
at the present after handling them over to the private sector, he
predicted.
</P>
<P>
The government began leasing out the trains as they were
incurring huge losses every year, and besides, the donor agencies
have also played a vital role in leasing out the trains, he
stated.
</P>
<P>
The BR has almost recovered the losses as it was earning 40
million taka (about 0.81 million U.S. dollars) from the public
service obligation and by leasing out some trains to the private
sector, he added.
</P>
<P>
The railway authorities first leased out services of 22 trains
to the private companies in 1998, according to the decision made
by the BR in a bid to increase the sagging revenue income, and the
result has been proved good. 
</P>
</TEXT>
