<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis Beats Venus Williams for TIG Tennis Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Martina Hingis is back on top
of the women's tennis world and overwhelmed Vennus Williams 6-4, 6-
0 in today's final of the 520,000 U.S. dollars TIG Tennis Classic
in San Diego,California.
</P>
<P>
After back-to-back embarrassing displays at the French Open and
Wimbledon, Hingis completed an impressive return to the No. 1
ranking and did not drop a set all week en route to her WTA Tour-
leading fifth title of the year, 24th of her career and second at
this event in three years. The second seed from Switzerland earned
80,000 U.S. dollars for the victory.
</P>
<P>
"I just got better and better as the tournament went on,"
Hingis said.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Hingis will reclaim the top spot in the WTA ranking
from American Linsday Davenport, whom the fourth-seeded Williams
beat in the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
After the players exchanged breaks in the first four games of
the match, Hingis moved into position to serve out the set as she
broke for a 5-4 lead. Hingis took the set as Williams netted a
backhand volley.
</P>
<P>
"Mentally it was important to win the first set," Hingis said.
"I thought Venus would have a hard time coming back after that."
</P>
<P>
As she has does often in the past, Williams fell apart in the
second set as Hingis displayed brilliant play from the baseline
and well-timed approaches to the net. The American teenager failed
to hold serve in her final four service games as Hingis eventually
served out her seventh win in 10 meetings with Williams.
</P>
<P>
"I was just too tired today," Williams said. "I've played three
weeks in a row on different continents. I wish I could have waited
to be tired till tomorrow."
</P>
<P>
Williams was denied her fifth title of 1999 for the second
straight week. She lost to Davenport in the final of last week's
Bank of the West Classic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
