<HEADLINE> Chinese Satellite Technology Is State-of-the-Art </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- China has modern research and
manufacturing facilities for small satellites and for their small
scale production, according to Xu Fuxiang, vice-president of the
China Space Technology Research Institute.
</P>
<P>
China's small satellite technology is state-of-the-art, he said,
and it has a comprehensive system that provides various service
and new applications for civilian and national defence uses.
</P>
<P>
"Experiment 5", which was launched in Taiyuan three months ago,
is operating smoothly and was the first "public platform" built by
the institute.
</P>
<P>
Other planned launches include "Marine 1", designed to study
constituents of ocean water that is set for 2001, and small
satellites to be used for navigation, mobile telecommunications,
and geographic monitoring, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
China's technology in this regard is both reliable and flexible,
he said. 
</P>
