<DOCNO> XIE19990809.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ground Fissure Discovered in Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The ground cracked as a result of a summer storm which lasted
about two hours in Shagou village of Jingyang county, about 30
meters to the north of Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi.
</P>
<P>
Local geologists have rushed to the site for field research,
who said the fissure runs across the whole village, and is of
varying depth and width.
</P>
<P>
The land fissure is a typical geological phenomenon in joint
areas between Loess Plateau and ravines, according to Wang Qiyi,
director of the Seismological Bureau of Xianyang city.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said the villagers will be relocated to ensure
their safety and a new village site has been chosen for the
present.
</P>
<P>
However, the villagers are still living in some makeshift
houses since the local government said it will take some time to
raise the over 800,000 yuan in relocation funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
