<DOCNO> XIE19990809.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Improving Construction Industry Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- China is working on laws and
regulations that deal with the construction industry to
standardize controls over the large construction business.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Construction, China is drafting a
series of laws, rules and regulations on residential buildings,
construction work, and contracting that are in accordance with the
Construction Law.
</P>
<P>
In addition, it is working on rules on construction safety and
engineering design and the City Planning Law is being revised.
Rules and regulations on urban drainage, gardening, central
heating, and utilization of gas have been submitted to the State
Council.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry source, China has passed some 49 laws
and rules on construction in recent years, which include the Urban
Real Estate Administration Law, Construction Law, Urban
Afforestation Rule, Urban Water Supply Rule, Urban Road
Administration Rule, and Registered Architect Rule, which have
helped put the country's construction business in order and have
helped urban construction and development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
