<HEADLINE> Main Venue for Fortune Forum Ready </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai International
Convention Center, specially designed as the prime venue for the '
99 Fortune Global Forum, is now completed.
</P>
<P>
The center is a 10-storey building with two large spherical
structures on either side, symbolizing the Earth's Eastern and
Western hemispheres.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the center began in July 1997 and was built
at a cost of 800 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The forum, scheduled for September 27-29 in Shanghai, is being
called "China: The Next 50 Years," and will focus on business
opportunities and challenges, economic issues, and practical
realities related to conducting business in China today and in the
next century.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai forum is expected to be the most important yet,
since the annual event was initiated in 1995. Previous forums were
held in Singapore, Barcelona, Bangkok, and Budapest.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 350 multinational firms have announced plans
to attend the Shanghai forum.  
</P>
</TEXT>
