<HEADLINE> New Inspection, Quarantine Bureau for Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The Exit and Entry Inspection and
Quarantine Bureau of Xiamen, a port city in east China's Fujian
Province, was inaugurated here today.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the establishment of the bureau is
meant to streamline coordination among several departments at the
state-level port, decrease business overlapping and reducing costs,
while also simplifying formerly tedious procedures for their
customers.
</P>
<P>
The bureau combines commodity inspection with the quarantine of
animals and plants and health quarantines for people. With the new
bureau, customers will have their clearance certificates completed
after following six separate procedures at one location.
</P>
<P>
The new organization will be vertically administered by the
State Exit and Entry Inspection and Quarantine Administration.
</P>
