<HEADLINE> Falun Gong Practitioners Break Away from Cult </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- More Falun Gong practitioners in
China have broken away from the cult, saying that they have been
fooled by its founder Li Hongzhi.
</P>
<P>
Song Xiujuan, head of the Falun Gong instruction station in the
northwestern city of Xi'an, vowed that she will have no more to do
with the cult.
</P>
<P>
She also called on fellow practitioners to see through the
political nature of the cult and the grave harm it caused the
country, and wake up from blind faith.
</P>
<P>
Many more people like Song across China have repented since the
government banned the cult last month.
</P>
<P>
Over 50 people gathered in the northeastern city of Anshan to
denounce the cult, and turned in various publications related to
Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
In the cities of Tangshan and Changchun large numbers of former
Falun Gong practitioners have also cut their ties with the cult.
</P>
<P>
As for those who still can't see the evil face of Li Hongzhi
and his Falun Gong, there are "help units" to assist them.
</P>
<P>
The coastal city of Tianjin has set up about 3,500 such units
in the neighborhoods and they are proving quite effective.
</P>
<P>
In Hohhot, capital of Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region,
hundreds of former practitioners now realize their errors in
believing in Li Hongzhi and his Falun Gong, and have broken away
from the cult. 
</P>
</TEXT>
