<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Restrictions on Foreign-Bank Yuan Business Eased </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- China's central bank announced
here today that foreign banks in Shanghai and Shenzhen are now
allowed to engage in yuan-based business in more localities, as
some restrictions concerning the scale of such business have been
eased as well.
</P>
<P>
A source from the People's Bank of China (PBOC) said that the
latest decision aims to increase foreign banks' yuan funding
source and promote the healthy development of their yuan business.
</P>
<P>
According to the PBOC's decision, foreign banks in Shanghai now
can develop yuan clients in east China's Jiangsu and Zhejiang
provinces, while those in Shenzhen can expand their yuan business
to south China's Guangdong Province and Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region and central-south China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
Previously, foreign banks could only deal in yuan on a trial
basis in Shanghai and Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
The ratio of foreign banks' yuan debt to foreign exchange debt
has been raised from 35 percent to 50 percent, and for the first
time foreign banks are allowed to do interbank transactions in the
yuan.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, foreign banks doing yuan business are
required to charge obligation and management fees when organizing
consortia, while branches of the same bank at different localities
are permitted to freely allocate and transfer their yuan accounts.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990809.0148 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Legal Scholars Slam Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Legal scholars in China's
largest city Shanghai recently lent their firm support to the
government's ban on the Falun Gong cult, saying that any illegal
organization which has disrupted the current stable social order
is doomed.
</P>
<P>
Professor Cao Jianming, head of the East China College of
Political Science and Law, pointed out that Li Hongzhi advocated
superstition and misled people into ignorance and occultism,
severely violating the guiding principle of China's Constitution,
which is Marxism, Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought, and Deng Xiaoping
Theory.
</P>
<P>
Cao held that what Li Hongzhi and his illegal organization
Falun Gong did has severely trampled the relevant laws of China,
and that Li should bear civil liability for Falun Dafa's role in
causing a large number of practitioners to lose their lives.
</P>
<P>
Shen Guoming, vice president of the Shanghai Academy of Social
Sciences, said that Li Hongzhi used his Falun Gong cult to stir up
followers to attack the government, newspapers, and TV stations
with the purpose of pressuring the Party and the government, which
totally violated Chinese laws.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese citizens should realize their rights according to
legal processes, and not by doing whatever they want to do," said
Shen.
</P>
<P>
Lawyer Li Guoji said that Li Hongzhi and his Falun Dafa
Research Society committed crimes, for the society is an illegal
unregistered organization which endangered the safety of the
country and caused the deaths of many people. Because of this, Li
Hongzhi should be severely punished, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
