<HEADLINE> PLA Publishing Houses Release Books Exposing Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Publishing houses affiliated to
the People's Liberation Army (PLA) have produced a series of books
recently advocating materialism and atheism, and criticizing Falun
Gong's advocacy of superstition and pseudo-science.
</P>
<P>
An 8-volume series entitled "Chinese People Should Wake up--the
True Face of Li Hongzhi and Falun Gong", published by the Long
March Publishing House, exposes the evil acts of Li Hongzhi, such
as organizing his followers to oppose science, society, and the
government.
</P>
<P>
Another book, "100 Anti-superstition Stories," a production of
the PLA Publishing House, upholds the high spirit of the ancient
Chinese people fighting against ghosts by selecting 100 pithy
stories from Chinese history.
</P>
<P>
Concurrently, the Public Security Bureau in the city of Anshan
in northeast China's Liaoning Province has cracked down on the
largest sellers of the Falun Gong books, and has confiscated 50,
000 yuan (about 6,000 U.S. dollars) worth of Falun Gong books and
audio and video tapes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
