<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Sharply Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks lost 221.59
points, or 1.68 percent, to close at 12,945.47 Monday on fears of
a U.S. interest rate rise.
</P>
<P>
Traders said that surging U.S. job numbers in July meant the
Federal Reserve would lift interest rates at its August 24 meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index went down 120.55 points, or 0.92 percent,
to open at 13,046.51 points Monday morning and finished the
morning session at 12,984.92 points.
</P>
<P>
The market turnover stood at 3.545 billion HK dollars (454
million U.S. dollars), 1.905 billion HK dollars (or 244 million U.
S. dollars) lower than Friday's turnover of 5.45 billion HK
dollars (698 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Finance Counter, Utilities, Properties and Commerce &AMP;
Industry were down 2.48 percent, 1.29 percent, 0.91 percent and 1.
50 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index fell 3.72 percent and the
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index lost 4.22 percent.
</P>
