<HEADLINE> Siamese Twin Die in Hospital in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manila, August 9 (Xinhua) -- A baby girl born with two heads,
three arms and three legs died after almost 13 hours at the
intensive care unit of the nursery section at a hospital in the
southern city of Bacolod Sunday morning, the Philippine News
Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The twins were born with their heads separated from each other
and their body clinging together down to their buttocks, while
their three arms swaying apart and their legs (left and right
beside them) formed into one, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Physicians had conducted the immediate cesarean section
operation after the child's mother felt labor pain. 
</P>
