<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Facing Great Challenges in Combating Drug: Jia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAOTOU, August 9 (Xinhua) -- China has become both a conduit
for international drug trafficking and a consumer of drugs, and
faces greater challenges in combating drug-related crimes than
ever, Minister of Public Security Jia Chunwang said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a national meeting on drug control, Jia pointed
out that China can not expect to solve this crisis brought about
by the worldwide flood of drugs in a short period of time.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, the police have cracked down
more than 110,000 drug-related cases and arrested nearly 140,000
suspects, according to the minister.
</P>
<P>
China has intensified its efforts to combat drugs since 1997,
and has achieved splendid results, he said, noting that a total of
15.4 tons of heroin and 3.9 tons of the synthetic narcotic
methamphetamine, or "ice," have been seized so far in two and a
half years.
</P>
<P>
Jia said China also is making an effort to help drug addicts
quit their habit by establishing and expanding drug rehabilitation
centers. The country has helped 320,000 drug addicts kick their
habit by compulsory means and has reeducated 210,000 through labor
since 1997.
</P>
<P>
According to Jia, in the 1980s, the drug problem in China was
mainly one of international drug trafficking, and only existed in
limited areas. The problem has become more serious with the spread
of drug abuse nationwide in the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China had nearly 600,000 registered
addicts last year, eight times the number in 1990, while the real
number is probably far above that figure.
</P>
<P>
"With expanding domestic drug consumption, illicit drug
trafficking is more serious, and now has organized and violent
tendencies," Jia said.
</P>
<P>
"It's a great challenge for China to control the flood of drug
and solve the drug problem," he admitted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990809.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
