<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Market Dragged Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- A sell-off in industrial stocks
pulled the Australian sharemarket lower Monday as investors became
convinced that the U.S. Federal Reserve will raise interest rates
later this month.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the benchmark all ordinaries index recovered from
its earlier lows to end 30.1 points weaker at 2,976.9 points.
Earlier it hit a low of 2,969.0 points.
</P>
<P>
The all industrial index lost 65.3 points to 5,121.8 points
while stronger commodity prices buoyed the resources sector which
closed 3.0 points higher at 1,309.6 points.
</P>
<P>
The interest rate-sensitive bank stocks were weaker almost
across the board, with the industry sub-index sliding 89.9 points
to 6,228.5.
</P>
<P>
National Australia Bank sagged 40 cents to 22.80 Australian
dollars, ANZ dropped 14 cents to 10.55 Australian dollars, Westpac
shed 13.1 cents to 9.75 Australian dollars and Commonwealth
slipped 32.5 cents to 24.27 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 337.81 million stocks traded for 908.56
million Australian dollars (599.65 million U.S. dollars), with
falling stocks outnumbering rising stocks 797 to 452 and 406
stocks steady. 
</P>
</TEXT>
