<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Close Marginally Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Karachi stocks ended marginally
lower Monday amid cautious tone where market players awaited the
outcome of the talks between Hubco, the largest private power
generating company, and the government over the power tariff
dispute.
</P>
<P>
The 100-share price index of Karachi Stock Exchange closed
Monday lower by 0.14 points, or 0.01 percent, to 1,207.75 points
from Friday's 1,207.89 points.
</P>
<P>
The volume traded Monday stood at 136.881 million shares
against Friday's 176.407 million shares.
</P>
<P>
The market players were prudent to take positions before the
Hubco talks yield any results, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 168 active issues, gainers narrowly outstripped 61
to 57 while 50 remained unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
