<HEADLINE> Cyclist Cotar Wins First Gold at Military World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, Croatia, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Cyclist Martin Cotar won
double honors for the host at the Military World Games when he
snatched the men's 30-km individual time trial here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old, who won the games' first gold medal, also
broke the duck for the Mediterranian country at the second edition
of the sports event organized by the International Military Sports
Council.
</P>
<P>
Cotar covered a 30-km section of the highway from Sesvete to
Sveta Helena, Croatia, in 36 minutes 28.14 seconds, with an
average speed of 50.5 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Manuel Quinziato came in a distant second at 38:14.91
while France's David Derepas won the bronze at 38:18.36.
</P>
<P>
At the first edition in Rome, Croatia only won a bronze in
boxing.
</P>
<P>
China's Shi Guijun finished 28th while Lou Jianshi 31st.
</P>
</TEXT>
