<HEADLINE> Sanchez-Lorenzo Celebrates First WTA Trophy in Sanex </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Maria Antonia Sanchez-
Lorenzo came from one set down to celebrate her first-ever WTA
trophy on Monday as she beat Denisa Chladkova of the Czech
Republic 6-7 (2-7), 6-4, 6-2 in Sanex Trophy open in Knokke,
Belgium.
</P>
<P>
The No. 4 seed lost the first set on a tiebreak Sunday before
rain fell. But the Barcelona-based player bounced back to overcome
the unseeded Czech in the Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old entered her first WTA final after she upset
second seed Silvija Talaja of Croatia and third seeded Slovak
Karina Habsudova. 
