<HEADLINE> Ford Motor Co. Opens Regional Headquarters in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 9 (Xinhua) -- U.S. auto giant Ford Motor Co.
Monday opened its regional headquarters in Thailand and voiced
confidence in the industry's prospects in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Ford Operations (Thailand) president David Snyder said at the
opening ceremony that Ford was optimistic about the industry's
market prospects within the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN), and would use Thailand as the base for its development.
</P>
