able to organize a smooth presidential election in 2000 and the
legislative elections in December 1999.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin sacked Serguey Stepashin from
the prime minister's post on Monday and replaced him with the
chief of federal security service (former KGB), Vladimir Putin.
