<HEADLINE> New Firms Set Up in Macao in First Half of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 9 (Xinhua) -- A total of 252 new companies were
established in Macao in the first half of this year, 0.4 percent
more than the same period of last year, the latest official
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released Monday by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show that the new companies involved a capital volume
of 77.2 million patacas (9.65 million U.S. dollars), which
decreased by 5.8 percent from the amount between January and June
of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Almost half of the new businesses were registered to manage
wholesale and retail sales, the maintenance of vehicles and
household goods, apartments, restaurants and hotels. And 14.9
percent of the new firms are involved in construction.
</P>
<P>
In the second quarter of this year, 134 new companies were
founded while 17 were closed. 
</P>
