<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 9 (Xinhua) - Ten persons died and 40 others were
injured when a truck plummeted into a 15-meter ravine in Mindanao,
southern Philippines, Saturday, reports reaching here said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Truck driver Aquino Omiple, 60, said the truck's brakes
malfunctioned when it negotiated a sharp downhill curve.
</P>
<P>
