<HEADLINE> Soft Drink Output Up in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Angola's soft drink production of
about 602, 000 hectoliters (hundred liters) in the first half of
1999 was three times of the 200,000 hectoliters in the same period
of 1998, the Journal of Angola newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Soft drink "Covic", made in Cabinda, a northwest enclave in
Angola, created a miracle with its production over 500,000
hectoliters, ranking first in the list of Angola's gas beverage
production.
</P>
<P>
Cuca BGI, a famous beer brand in Angola, ranks the second in
the list, with a supply to market of 328,000 hectoliters,
decreasing by 25 percent from the amount in the second half of
1998 (450,000 hectoliters).
</P>
<P>
The first half of 1999 saw sharp falls in the production of
other brand beers. The outputs of Sorea and Frasal were less than
8,000 hectoliters, while Sefa stopped its production.
</P>
<P>
But wines are still popular in the country, with a growth rate
of 264 percent as compared with the production in the second half
of 1998.  Wine producing companies, such as Cifal and Sofogor,
had revenues of 76 billion and 440 million readjusted kwanza
(25,000 u.s. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
