<HEADLINE> Some Macao Legislators Apply to Go Through Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Some elected members of the current
Macao Legislative Assembly have applied to enter the first
Legislative Council of the future Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
On Monday, nine elected legislators went to the Macao office of
the Secretariat of the Preparatory Committee for the Macao SAR and
filled in forms which confirm their qualification of becoming
legislators of the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Legislative Assembly consists of 23 members,
including seven appointed by the governor and 16 elected by
individual voters or certain social organizations.
</P>
<P>
The elected legislators are required to go to the Macao office
of the secretariat from August 9 to 20 in person and fill in
qualification confirmation forms, which will be examined at the
plenary session of the Preparatory Committee to be held at the end
of this month.
</P>
<P>
Comprising the same number of 23, the first Legislative Council
of the Macao SAR will be formally set up on December 20 when China
resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Macao and the Macao SAR
is established. 
</P>
</TEXT>
