<HEADLINE> France to Increase Train Service on Eclipse Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The French state railway company,
the SNCF, will increase by 30 percent the trains from Paris to the
cities within the total eclipse belt in northern France, where the
sun will be completely obscured by the moon for two minutes on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The SNCF announced on Monday that more trains are expected to
arrive in Le Havre and Dieppe in Normandy, and Noyon, Laon, Amiens
and Reims in other northern provinces.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the SNCF will send a special high speed train from
Lyon to Picardie on that day to allow travelers watch the rare
celestial phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
The SNCF will distribute observation sunglasses at the railway
stations and offer special discount to passengers riding classic
trains going from Paris to the zone of observation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
