<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Technical Officers Criticize Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Technical officers from the
Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) and the People's Armed
Police are using their scientific knowledge to unmask and
criticize the evil nature of Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
Chen Qizhi, a leading expert on rocket engines, said that the
earth is only a small planet in the solar system and the beautiful
home of mankind, instead of a "trash station" claimed by Li
Hongzhi, the founder of Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
He said that scientists have the responsibility to defend and
popularize scientific knowledge and educate people to break away
from superstition.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi's Falun Dafa (another name for Falun Gong) opposes
modern sciences and human civilization, said technical officers at
a naval base, adding that without science and technology they
could not have scored so many achievements in the past 40 years.
</P>
<P>
Yang Jin, a research fellow with the Military Academy of
Medical Sciences of the PLA, said that with the development of
modern medical sciences, most diseases can be cured or controlled.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi's advocacy of cure for diseases through practising
Falun Gong is a sheer fallacy, and has led to a number of deaths,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from further criticizing superstition and pseudo-science,
the technical officers have also made great efforts to popularize
knowledge of science within the armed forces and the general
public. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990809.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Scientists Urged to Develop Space Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Indian Vice President Krishan
Kant Monday urged scientists to develop advanced indigenous space
technology to safeguard national security, saying space
surveillance systems would dominate future battles.
</P>
<P>
India "should possess indigenously developed technologies
advanced enough to enable us to confidently meet such threats",
Kant said after presenting the Gujar Mal Modi award to noted space
scientist and former chairman of Indian Space Research
Organization U. R. Rao here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Since space technologies play a crucial role in safeguarding
national security, such technologies were needed urgently, he
said, adding that space surveillance systems dominate battles on
land, water and air.
</P>
<P>
Citing the examples of the recent wars in Kosovo and the Gulf,
he said exclusive access to space technologies enabled the United
States and its allies to wage war with very less casualties to
their own side.
</P>
<P>
The Indian vice president cautioned against attempts of
advanced nations to prevent other countries from developing space
technology and monopolize the power and benefits of the
technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
