<HEADLINE> French Union Rejects Work Order to Truck Drivers on Eclipse Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The French labor union Force
Ouvriere (FO) rejected on Monday an order by managers of truck
drivers that trucks should remain on the road during the impending
eclipse on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
FO said the appeal, made by the French National Union of Bosses
in the Trucking Industry (UNOSTRA) operating in the central region
of Bourgogne and the eastern region of Franche-Comte, is "
irresponsible."
</P>
<P>
The French Ministry of Transport issued an order banning heavy
trucks from moving on the roads during the hours of eclipse from
10:00 a.m. till 15:00 p.m. on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The northern Part of France will see a total eclipse of the sun
by the moon in the early afternoon on that day, while all of
France will be affected by the eclipse to differing degrees.
</P>
<P>
The UNOSTRA in Bourgogne and Franche-Comte said that trucks
should keep moving during the time of eclipse, because there are
not enough parking spaces.
</P>
<P>
The FO also condemned the decision by UNOSTRA that truckers
would not be paid during the time they were not moving. 
</P>
