<HEADLINE> Anthology on Materialism, Atheism Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- A book titled "Marx, Engels,
Lenin, Stalin, Mao Zedong, Deng Xiaoping and Jiang Zemin on
Materialism and Atheism" has just been published here.
</P>
<P>
It was compiled by the Party Literature Research Center of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and the
Compilation and Translation Bureau of the CPC Central Committee,
and published by the Central Literature Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The 60,000-character anthology is in two parts: The first part,
consisting of four chapters, includes remarks of Marx, Engels,
Lenin and Stalin on the basic theories of materialism and atheism,
the essence and social influence of religion and the proletarian
parties' attitude to religion.
</P>
<P>
The second part includes Mao Zedong, Deng Xiaoping and Jiang
Zemin's discourses on the Marxist world outlook, and views on
religion and on the promotion of science while eliminating
superstition. The latter part of the collection is published for
the first time.  
</P>
