<HEADLINE> Liaoning Have No Interest for League Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, Liaoning Province, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning
Fushun head coach Zhang Yin did not think the Chinese first-
division league title do any good to his young team.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said on Monday that he had no interest to win the league
trophy as his team was only promoted to the league for the first
time, despite it overtook Shandong Luneng for the top place after
its 2-1 win over Qingdao Hainiu on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"My squad is too young to handle the easy victory," Zhang said.
"The players could be arrogant after triumph and the league title
will do more harm than good to the rebuilding of the young team."
</P>
<P>
Liaoning, who promoted to the top-level league after it won the
second division last season, had won all the latest five round
matches since July 18 and collected 34 points, one point adrift
over the second-placed Shandong.
</P>
<P>
"The past five round opponents are handful to us, and the big
challenge will come in the rest of the season," Zhang added.
</P>
<P>
Qu Shengxin topped the league's scorers list with 15 goals,
alongwith Zhang Yuning, top striker in the China's Olympic team,
and Li Jinyu, who had scored four goals in five games after he
came back from French side Nancy on loan, to compose of the most
fearful attacking force in the league.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning will travel to Guangzhou to meet Guangzhou Songri in
the next round. 
</P>
